== Summary ==

The [[Ada Programming/Pragmas|pragma]] '''Inline''' specifies that a subprogram should be expanded inline when called in code.

== Example ==

 {{Ada/kw|function}} My_Function {{Ada/kw|return}} Integer {{Ada/kw|is}} {{Ada/kw|begin}}
   {{Ada/kw|return}} 1+2; {{Ada/--|A simple function suitable for inlining}}
 {{Ada/kw|end}} My_Function;
 {{Ada/pragma|inline}}(My_Function);
 ...
 Some_Variable := My_Function; {{Ada/--|Will be expanded by compiler.}}

