== Summary ==

The [[Ada Programming/Pragmas|pragma]] '''Import''' directs the compiler to use code or data objects written in a foreign computer language.

Which foreign languages are supported depends on the compiler implementation. Typically [[C Programming|C]], [[C++ Programming|C++]], Cobol, and [[Fortran]] are supported.

== Example ==

 {{Ada/C/*|C file}}
 {{Ada/C/kw|int}} my_C_function() {
   {{Ada/C/kw|return}} 1;
 }

 {{Ada/--|Ada File}}
 {{Ada/kw|function}} My_C_Function {{Ada/kw|return}} Integer;
 {{Ada/pragma|Import}}
   (Convention    => C,
    Entity        => My_C_Function,
    External_Name => "my_C_function" );
 ...
 Some_Variable := My_C_Function; {{Ada/--|Ada uses a foreign language like a pro!}}
                                 {{Ada/--|Huzzah!}}

