{{Ada/Navigation|Pragmas|Normalize Scalars}}
__TOC__

== Summary ==

The [[Ada Programming/Pragmas|pragma]] '''Normalize_Scalars''' directs the compiler to initialize otherwise uninitialized scalar variables with predictable values. If possible, the compiler will choose out-of-range values.

== Example ==

 {{Ada/pragma|Normalize_Scalars}};
 ...
 My_Variable : Positive; {{Ada/--|Oops, forgot to initialize this variable.}}
                         {{Ada/--|The compiler (may) initialize this to 0}}
 ...
 {{Ada/--|Oops, using a variable before it is initialized!}}
 {{Ada/--|An exception should be raised here, since the compiler}}
 {{Ada/--|initialized the value to 0 - an out-of-range value for the Positive type.}}
 Some_Other_Variable := My_Variable;

