&lsaquo;<small> [[Australian History/Preface|Back to the Preface]]</small>

While Australia is a young nation, its development over a period of little more than two centuries has been rapid and remarkable.

This book is a social, cultural, political, economic, and military history of Australia covering the nation's history from the continent's pre-European era through to the present day. It focuses on the early history of the Colonies and key events in their history prior to Federation, as well as each of the decades - since Federation - to the present day.

<small>[[Australian History/First Settlers|Forward to the First Settlers]] </small>&rsaquo;



{{BookCat}}

&lsaquo;<small> [[Australian History/Contents|Return to the Contents]]</small><br>
&lsaquo;<small> [[Australian History/1970s|Back to The Whitlam - Fraser Era]]</small>

The 1980s have been described by some as a decade of excess. Australian entrpreneurs including Alan Bond, and Christopher Skase would rise to prominence and acclaim during the decade when "greed was good". However, the excesses would end following the 1987 Stockmarket Crash, and the recession which followed in its wake. It was also a decade which, under the Hawke / Keating Federal Government, saw significant economic reforms, which would continue into the [[Australian History/1990s|1990s]].

<small>[[Australian History/1990s|Economic Rationalism, Reform, and the Backlash]] </small>&rsaquo;



