== Words == I tried to use Japanese in Gmail to immerse myself. However I found out that only most of the katakana made sense for me :). I thought that the kanjis in Gmail forms a subset of kanjis found in computing, so I thought this guide can also be useful as a specific kanji list. I'm sorry that right now I can only give meaning to the words in katakana. [[User:Agro1986|Agro1986]] 07:49, 24 September 2005 (UTC) : Almost all these words are used by most email clients and are not specific to Gmail. Should we be making a general email guide? : I went ahead and filled in the readings and meanings. For the individual kanji, I just added the 'on' reading so they'll be easier to look up. I don't use Gmail, so I wasn't sure what to make of the "introduce a friend to Gmail" vocab. Maybe 紹介(introduce) should be reworded using "invite" or "invitation" here. Feel free to fix the translations up. You could probably get away with just copying the button names from English Gmail. : --[[User:ToothingLummox|ToothingLummox]] 09:12, 24 September 2005 (UTC)
